def calc_fuel(n):
    time = n * 11
    lava, blaze = divmod(time, 800)
    blaze, coal = divmod(blaze, 120)
    coal, wood = divmod(coal, 80)
    wood, stick = divmod(wood, 15)
    
    return {'lava': lava, 'blaze rod': blaze, 'coal': coal, 'wood': wood, 'stick': stick}

d = [
  (800, "lava"),
  (120, "blaze rod"),
  (80, "coal"),
  (15, "wood"),
  (1, "stick")
]

def calc_fuel(n):
    n *= 11
    r = {}
    for a, b in d:
        r[b] = n // a
        n %= a
    return r

def calc_fuel(n):
    result={}
    wholeTime=n*11
    result["lava"]=wholeTime//800
    wholeTime-=800*result["lava"]
    result["blaze rod"]=wholeTime//120
    wholeTime-=120*result["blaze rod"]
    result["coal"]=wholeTime//80
    wholeTime-=80*result["coal"]
    result["wood"]=wholeTime//15
    wholeTime-=15*result["wood"]
    result["stick"]=wholeTime//1
    return result
